	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=27454><span id=Scholar>Baila the Wise</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>46 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.47]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>No one would equip this when meleeing, but that's not necessarily the point. People would equip this when buying/selling to get better prices. They would equip it when learning a new skill due to the int/wis stats, and also because str plus helps them lug around the stuff they need to practice the skill if it requires components.<br><br>Now yes, a caster would probably benefit from carrying this in an ammo slot where a melee type wouldn't, but it doesn't mean it's not beneficial to melee types. What is beneficial to all classes is the weight reducing bag it can summon.</p>&nbsp;<br>Dienia Tallis - Druid<br>Baila - retired Shaman<br>Addria - Enchanter<br>Iantha - Cleric<br>Phedre - Monk<br>Pyria - Wizard</td></td></tr>
